annotation.TEXT: To be continued...
Yes way. This is totally a remake of world 3-4 from SMB3! However, where's the fish in the pond here?
Hey, where'd the switch palace go? Also, I see a new level dot has appeared on an already revealed path. Surely I can enter that level, right?
Well, I think I'll do one more level over here today. It's "LEAVE!", which existed in the previous version of this hack.
Same old. Same old.
Heck, yeah. Wrestling an Urchin without getting hurt, somehow.
Huh. For some reason I was expecting that to be Jesus water. Wait a minute... No way...
Well, first let's deal with the level I'm on. It translates to "World Three-four". Huh... I didn't realize I was this far into world 3 already... These worlds are short, man!
Oh, hello there, fake wall. I was just going to lean against the wall then press R to peek ahead, but I guess I don't have to.
Oh, well. Let's move on. Now, I remember seeing a Yoshi coin below as I was chasing Yoshi a moment ago, but...
Oh, you little sneak! The middle of the pipe is fake!
Same old. Same old.
Okay, can I stop getting knocked off Yoshi for just a few seconds, please?
Double gulp! Also, I'm glad I landed squarely on Yoshi there!

Unfortunately, these note blocks on the right are totally real, and the pipe is perfectly solid, too. There doesn't appear to be a way to reach that ? block up there, and it's not even a backwards ? block either, so it probably does hold something.
Wait, that fake moon is different! It's upside-down now!
Okay, now these backwards note blocks on the left are obviously fake.
I know there's a Lakitu that appears here in SMB3's 3-4.
Huzzah! There is a wall! Now I can get Yoshi back! Wow, normally a wall beyond the goal is pointless, but here it made a difference!
Also, why is there vertical scrolling? And, you could've safely set this level's time limit to 300 instead of 400.
Double gulp!
However, I think I'll save "Our last challenge" for next time! (Hmm... I probably could've squeezed it into this episode, though. Oh, well.)
Oh, I betcha this pipe is exit-enabled.
...It was on the other side of this green pipe. However, the pipe is solid, and I can't enter it, so how do I...
BARF! Stupid Chuck...
Wah! Stupid bullet...
I still gotta check every pipe... (Though I would've lost Yoshi there if that pipe did lead somewhere.)
Alright, so this allows me access to this level dot on the mainland that I passed by before. Oh, and is that another Yellow Switch Palace that I might be playing soon?
Wah! Oh, nuts. I think I've really lost Yoshi this time, unless Greenman was kind enough to include a wall over here...
And that time it did! I have no idea how the game let me stomp that last koopa!

Alright, now let's not get shot in the face by a bullet again. (I think I'm lucky that I was able to retrieve Yoshi right away there, because I don't think there was a wall to my left to keep him in-bounds.)
Oh, man. I almost don't want to hit this P-switch, because it'll ruin the music, but I've gotta show off the P-switch coins here!
Bah, Bob-omb!
Well, it would appear that I have just one level left, which is the castle way over here on the right.
BGM: Touhou 6 - Cirno's Theme - Beloved Tomboyish Daughter
Hey there dudes, and welcome back to some insane island somewhere! Now, let's explore "Some Lake"...
Ah, there we go!
Oh, whew. Yoshi was never in any danger of going out of bounds, thanks to these pipes.
Oh, man! It's this music again! Dude!
Heck, yeah! I was aiming for a 4 there! I wanted to clear the level with the clock at 299 so I'd get a 1-up for lining up the digits, and I wanted a 4 so that I'd end up at exactly 99 stars!
Let me just ludicrously speed through this bonus game here...
Also, I think this ledge is two blocks higher than usual.
Same old. Same old.
Okay, I've fully reflowered now.
Yep, I glitched this fish. I think he's still edible, though.
Only the right end of the pipe is solid, but I can walk right through the rest of it!
Meh. You never know when somebody will hide something to the left of the start point.
I guess I'll take a spare mushroom now.
Alright, this level's done.
...Except, I don't stop on that level dot as I walk across it, and even if I'm ABYX-ing like crazy as I walk across it, I can't enter it.
Whoa! I was trying to do something fancy there, but it didn't work quite right.
Well, except for the music, and the fake moons now being turned upside-down, this level appears to be exactly the same as last time.
Why is it that you tend to stick to slopes underwater when trying to ascend while holding down or while carrying an item?
Wah! YOSHIII!!! I see some stuff up above that I'll want to check out, but first, I've gotta see if I can retrieve Yoshi! Please let there be a wall or something for him to bounce off of...
Gotta check every pipe. Even the icy-colored pipes, in case someone did some Map16 editing to make exit-enabled versions of them...
Oh, man! This music! Dude! This music, man! This music!
The 1-up's here like usual. However, shouldn't there be a Lakitu around here, too?
Yep, that's a perfect!
Same old. Same old.
There are Yoshi coins added to this level, which is cool.
And now to eat this rotten fish...
To be honest, I was expecting to be unable to stop on or enter that level dot. But, why did that level dot appear there in the first place? An OW event glitch, perhaps?
Whoa, hey there munchers. Good thing I'm on Yoshi!
